             Geologic Information about the Mid-Atlantic States

   "Geologic Information about the Mid-Atlantic States" highlights
   selected research on the States of Delaware, the District of Columbia,
   Maryland, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Virginia, and West
   Virginia and offers links to other online resources for each State.

   DELAWARE
     * Chesapeake Bay Ecosystem Program
     * Current Regional Earthquake Information
     * 1996 Seismic Hazard Maps
     * Delaware State Minerals Information

   DISTRICT OF COLUMBIA
     * Chesapeake Bay Ecosystem Program
     * Ecosystem Trends and Response: Chesapeake Bay (fact sheet)
     * Current Regional Earthquake Information
     * 1996 Seismic Hazard Maps
     * Geologic Radon Potential Map - Washington, D.C. Metro Area

   MARYLAND
     * http://www.mgs.md.gov/esic/geo/index.html - Index to Online
       Geologic Maps (1968)
     * Chesapeake Bay Ecosystem Program
